  <h2>What is a Network Protocol?</h2>
  <p>A <strong>Network Protocol</strong> is a standardized set of rules, formats, and procedures that govern how computers and devices format, transmit, receive, and interpret data packets across a network. Without protocols, devices from different manufacturers running different operating systems would be unable to decode each other's electronic signals, rendering communication impossible.</p>
  
  <p>Protocols exist at every layer of the network stack. They handle everything from error correction and flow control to data formatting, encryption, and logical address resolution.</p>

